    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.20.5-7_0001a"/>
                
                <note type="curatorial">Missouri Collection</note>
                
                <opener>
                    <dateline>Great Bend, Kan. Aug 12, 194<unclear>2</unclear></dateline>
                
                    <salute>Dear Mr. Neihardt,-</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>In 1939, I think, I had the pleasure of hearing you speak at a Rotary Club in Illinois on your writings about the Indians. Later I bought a copy of "The Messiah" and read it several times, I liked it so well that I gave a copy to my daughter, Mrs. John Trimmell, 1219 Munroe St, Great Bend, Kan. She in turn liked it so well that she purchased a complete set of your writings and you very kindly autographed each book. These she kept as a present to me, to be given to me on my return from <del/><unclear>China</unclear>. After 37 years in <unclear>China</unclear> we are remaining in the United States, and I shall read all your books carefully, probably several times, and I am anticipating much pelasure in doing so.</p> 
                
                <p>In <unclear>China</unclear>, as teacher, preacher, and           
                
                <!--page likely missing here-->
                    
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.20.5-7_0003a"/>
                
                    <fw type="curatorial">7</fw>
                    
                    not a few close friends in <unclear/> ethnic groups, who were glad to tell me in many heart-to-heart talks how they felt. Studying their folk-stories and other literature helped me to better understand their ways of thinking and expressing themselves. Probably these experiences have helped me to appreciate what you have done in studying and writing about the American Indians. I congratulate you on what you have accomplished and consider that you have rendered a <unclear>valuable</unclear> service to mankind.</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>With best wishes, I am
                    very sincerely yours</salute>
                    <signed>David C Graham</signed>
                
                    <address>
                        <addrLine>address 125 Highland Parkway</addrLine>
                            <addrLine>Rochester, New York</addrLine>
                    </address>
                </closer>
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.20.5-7_0003b"/>
                
